verbose_text: In the presence of DMU (1 mM), 1 mM H 2 O 2 and 0.02 mM Cu (II) produced only a weak reduction of fast and slow potassium outward current of 12.5% and 10.26%, respectively (XREF_FIG A), which was significantly smaller than the reduction of 70.15% and 69.24% in the absence of DMU.
evidence: Cu(II) produced only a weak reduction of fast and slow potassium
